inclair's campaign while also capturing the turbulent political mood of the 1930s. Employing his trademark muckraking style, Sinclair exposes the conspiracies of power that ensured big-money control over the media and other powerful institutions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aGovernorsxElectionxHistoryx20th centuryxCalifornia. 0aGovernorszCaliforniaxElectionxHistoryy20th century. 0aMass mediaxPolitical aspectsxHistoryx20th centuryxCalifornia. 0aMass mediaxPolitical aspectszCaliforniaxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / West (AK, CA, CO, HI, ID, MT, NV, UT, WY).2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520913523?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520913523423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520913523/original  aEBA_EMB  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles